# Agent Workflow CLI Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials

# ================================
# OpenAI Configuration (Required)
# ================================
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_api_key_here
AI_MODEL=gpt-4o
AI_MAX_TOKENS=4000

# ================================
# JIRA Configuration (Required)
# ================================
JIRA_HOST=your-company.atlassian.net
JIRA_USERNAME=your_jira_username
JIRA_PASSWORD=your_jira_password_or_pat

# ================================
# GitHub Configuration (Optional)
# ================================
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_token_here

# ================================
# Configuration Notes
# ================================
# 
# OpenAI API Key:
# - Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# - Required for generating coding prompts
# - Models: gpt-4o (best quality), gpt-4o-mini (good balance), gpt-3.5-turbo (fastest)
#
# JIRA Configuration:
# - JIRA_HOST: Your JIRA hostname WITHOUT https:// (e.g., company.atlassian.net)
# - JIRA_USERNAME: Your JIRA username/email
# - JIRA_PASSWORD: Your JIRA password or Personal Access Token (PAT recommended)
# - For PAT setup, run: agent-workflow setup-jira-pat
#
# GitHub Token (Optional):
# - Get from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# - Required only if you plan to use GitHub integration features
# - Permissions needed: repo, read:org
#
# Security Notes:
# - Never commit this file to version control
# - Use environment variables in production
# - Rotate tokens regularly
# - Personal Access Tokens are more secure than passwords 
